<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
The Pulau Tioman specimens agree well with figures of 
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Ischyroceridae" genus="Ericthonius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ericthonius pugnax" order="Amphipoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pugnax">Ericthonius pugnax</taxonomicName>
from 
<bibRefCitation author="Walker, AO" journalOrPublisher="Report of the Government of Ceylon Pearl Oyster Fishery of the Gulf of Manaar" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="229 - 300" title="Report on Amphipoda collected by Professor Herdman, at Ceylon, in 1902." volume="17" year="1904">Walker (1904)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Nagata, K" journalOrPublisher="Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="163 - 182" title="Preliminary notes on benthic gammaridean Amphipoda from the Zostera region of Mihara Bay, Seto Inland Sea, Japan." volume="8" year="1960">Nagata (1960</bibRefCitation>
, 1965c), 
<bibRefCitation author="Ledoyer, M" journalOrPublisher="Centre National de la Recherche Scientifique-Paris" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" title="Faune de Madagascar. Crustaces Amphipodes Gammariens; Families des Haustoriidae a' Vitjazianidae." volume="59" year="1982 c">Ledoyer (1982c)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Moore, PG" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="705 - 732" title="Taxonomic observations on the genera Xenocheria Haswell and Ericthonius Milne-Edwards (Crustacea: Amphipoda) from Australian coastal waters." url="10.1080/00222938800770461" volume="22" year="1988">Moore (1988)</bibRefCitation>
. This species seems to have a wide-ranging distribution as far as the Arabian Sea. From closer examination of the specimens, the males not only have distally bidentate carpal spur of gnathopod 2 but also a mixture of single dentate carpal spur (see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Nagata, K" journalOrPublisher="Publications of the Seto Marine Biological Laboratory" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="163 - 182" title="Preliminary notes on benthic gammaridean Amphipoda from the Zostera region of Mihara Bay, Seto Inland Sea, Japan." volume="8" year="1960">Nagata 1960</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ledoyer, M" journalOrPublisher="Recueil des Travaux de la Station Marine Endoume, Fascicule hors serie Supplement" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="179 - 182" title="Amphipodes tubicoles des feuilles des herbiers de phanerogames marines de la region de Tulear (Madagascar)." volume="9" year="1969">Ledoyer 1969</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ledoyer, M" journalOrPublisher="Mexico" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="171 - 200" title="Faune mobile des herbiers de phanerogames marines (Holodule et Thalassia) de la lagune de terminus (Mexique, Campeche). II. Les Gammariens (Crustacea). An. Inst. Cienc. del Mar y Limnol. Univ. Nal. Auton." volume="13" year="1986">1986</bibRefCitation>
). As mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Moore, PG" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="705 - 732" title="Taxonomic observations on the genera Xenocheria Haswell and Ericthonius Milne-Edwards (Crustacea: Amphipoda) from Australian coastal waters." url="10.1080/00222938800770461" volume="22" year="1988">Moore (1988)</bibRefCitation>
the carpal bidentate spur of ganthopod 2 will eventually be lost in hyperadult males. Unfortunately the stipulation over hyper adult morphological changes has brought several descriptions of new species that actually represented a single species (i.e 
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Ischyroceridae" genus="Ericthonius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ericthonius macrodactylus" order="Amphipoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrodactylus">Ericthonius macrodactylus</taxonomicName>
). Prior to this, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ledoyer, M" journalOrPublisher="Recueil des Travaux de la Station Marine Endoume, Fascicule hors serie Supplement" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="179 - 182" title="Amphipodes tubicoles des feuilles des herbiers de phanerogames marines de la region de Tulear (Madagascar)." volume="9" year="1969">Ledoyer (1969)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Ischyroceridae" genus="Ericthonius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ericthonius macrodactylus" order="Amphipoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrodactylus">Ericthonius macrodactylus</taxonomicName>
as a hyperadult form of 
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Ischyroceridae" genus="Ericthonius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ericthonius pugnax" order="Amphipoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pugnax">Ericthonius pugnax</taxonomicName>
. Examination of the Pulau Tioman specimens confirms the presence of this hyper adult morphology: that the basis of pereopod 5 possesses a strongly developed posterodistal lobe. The Pulau Tioman specimens are undoubtedly assigned to 
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Ischyroceridae" genus="Ericthonius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ericthonius pugnax" order="Amphipoda" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pugnax">Ericthonius pugnax</taxonomicName>
and constitute the first record of this species for Peninsular Malaysia.
</paragraph>
